The paper focuses on improving the usability of privacy settings in Facebook, which is a human-computer interaction (HCI) problem. Therefore, cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social networks (cs.SI), which are closely related to privacy concerns. Additionally, the paper discusses the aggregation and retrieval of personal data, which falls under the category of data management (cs.SD). Finally, the paper proposes a new privacy interface, which involves the use of color coding and common practices, which could be classified under the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
